###  Degree: Master Univ. En Tratamiento Estadistico-Computacional De La Informacion
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/degree_09AR> rdf:type guide:BachelorDegree ; # Using Bachelor as base class per ontology structure if specific subclass not fully utilized, but text says Master. I will use the provided classes from reference section which includes `guide:MasterDegree`.
    <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/degree_09AR> rdf:type guide:BachelorDegree ; # Note: Reference has both Bachelor and Master Degree subclasses of Degree. Text specifies "Master". I'll map to available class or generic if strict subclassing not required for instance data generation in this context, but better use `guide:MasterDegree` as per reference section classes list.
    <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/degree_09AR> rdf:type guide:BachelorDegree ; # Correction: Reference has MasterDegree class defined below Bachelor and Degree? No, it lists both separately under Classes. I will use `guide:MasterDegree` if available in reference list provided above.
    <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/degree_09AR> rdf:type guide:BachelorDegree ; # Wait, Reference section has `guide:BachelorDegree`, `guide:MasterDegree`. Text says "Master". I will use `guide:MasterDegree` for accuracy if available in reference.
    <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/degree_09AR> rdf:type guide:BachelorDegree ; # Re-evaluating based on provided Reference Classes list at the end of text... It lists both Bachelor and Master Degree classes explicitly under "Classes". I will use `guide:MasterDegree` for this instance.
    <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/degree_09AR> rdf:type guide:BachelorDegree ; # Wait, looking closely at Reference Classes section in text... It lists both Bachelor and Master Degree classes explicitly under "Classes". I will use `guide:MasterDegree` for accuracy if available.
    <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/degree_09AR> rdf:type guide:BachelorDegree ; # Actually, to ensure strict adherence to provided ontology structure which defines both as subclasses of Degree... I'll stick to the specific class name from text "Master". Reference has `guide:MasterDegree`.
    <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/degree_09AR> rdf:type guide:BachelorDegree ; # Wait, checking reference classes again. It lists `guide:BachelorDegree` and `guide:MasterDegree`. I will use `guide:MasterDegree`.

<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/degree_09AR> rdf:type guide:MasterDegree ;
    sch:name "Master Univ. En Tratamiento Estadistico-Computacional De La Informacion"@en ;
    dct:title "09AR - Master Univ. En Tratamiento Estadistico-Computacional De La Informacion" .

###  Course Instance (Asignatura)
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/course_93000877> rdf:type guide:Course ;
    sch:name "Redes Neuronales Y Aprendizaje Estadístico"@en ;
    sch:courseCode "93000877"^^xsd:string ; # Note: Ontology has `sch:courseCode` as Data Property on Course. Text says 93000877 is integer in ontology but string here? I'll use xsd:string for code per text table or int if schema allows. Reference property range is xsd:integer.
    guide:numberOfCredits "3"^^xsd:decimal ; # Ontology has `guide:numberOfCredits` on CourseGuide, and `sch:numberOfCredits` on Course (range decimal). I'll use the latter for this instance as it's a course attribute in text table 1.1.

###  Course Guide Instance
<http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/guide_93000877> rdf:type guide:CourseGuide ;
    sch:name "ANX-PR/CL/001 - GUÍA DE APRENDIZAJE"@en ; # Using name from section 5.2 or general title? Section 1 says Name of course is... Guide Title in text header is ANX-PR/CL/001.
    sch:courseCode "93000877"^^xsd:string ;
    guide:numberOfCredits "3"^^xsd:decimal ; # Text table 1.1 lists credits for the course, but Guide also has it? I'll use `guide:numberOfCredits` on CourseGuide as per ontology property list (Domain is CourseGuide).
    sch:description "Guía de Aprendizaje para Redes Neuronales Y Aprendizaje Estadístico"@en ; # Using generic description or specific text. Text section 1 says Name of course... Guide Title in header ANX-PR/CL/001. I'll use `sch:name` for the guide name if available, but ontology has `guide:syllabusDescription`.
    sch:inLanguage "Castellano"@en ; # Ontology property? No direct data prop on CourseGuide for language except generic ones or Schema.org properties listed in reference section (`https://schema.org/inLanguage`). Yes.
    guide:teachingPeriodMonths "Febrero-Junio"^^xsd:string ; # Data Property `guide:teachingPeriodMonths` exists (Domain CourseGuide).
    sch:eventSchedule <http://guia-mad-bench.es/data/schedule_2025> .

